result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were revoked, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Cassie M Smith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Cassie M Smith in court with attorney Paul M Goetz.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 9:09 a.m. Agreement stated - Def will plead to cts 3 & 5.  Ct 3 - defer judgment 2 yrs, written agreement prepared, if successfully completes, hrg on 1/16/18 @ 1:00 p.m. will dismiss. Ct 5 - withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, counseling deemed appropriate, court costs. State asking 30 days jail, Def free to argue jail time. Costs will include DNA. Atty Goetz agrees, asks for huber privileges for employment and/or childcare, asks start date in 45-60 days at discretion of PO for Def to look for employment. Def agrees. Plea quest. reviewed. Plea to ct 3 - no contest. Plea to ct 5 - no contest. Cts 1, 2, 4 dismissed and read in on motion of State. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Goetz satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas. Ct 3 - Court approves and signs deferred entry of judgment agreement. Ct 5 - State heard on sentencing. Atty Goetz heard on sentencing, asks 3 days credit. State asks any credit be only if revoked. Questions by the Court. Statement by Def. Court finds guilty of ct 5. Sentencing remarks by the Court. Orders on ct 5: will follow agreement, Sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge, AODA and follow through and counseling as recommended, credit for 3 days if revoked, probation is concurrent with probation already serving. Return bond to poster. Court reviews considerations for jail time, orders 20 days jail, huber as allowed by jail, report no later than 6 p.m. on 3/10/16. Def advised of voting and firearms restrictions.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Discussion regarding credit if revoked, Court reserves Def right to clarify amount of credit if revoked. Bond will be converted to signature bond $500.  Review hearing scheduled for January 16, 2018 at 01:00 pm.
